<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-02-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-02-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="471" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862.852/71</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 10018</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-02-14">February 14, 1940</date>.<lb/>[Received
                                February 19.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to record below a report
                            made to me by the Commercial Attaché relative to the proposed purchase
                            of the <hi rend="italic">Tine Asmussen</hi>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“I asked Professor Silva Herzog, Manager of Distribuidora de
                                    Petroleos Mexicanos, on February 14th, if he had purchased the
                                    German tanker, <hi rend="italic">Tine Asmussen</hi> from W. R.
                                    Davis. He said that the matter stood just where it had been for
                                    some time and, consequently, the vessel had not been purchased.
                                    He said that the price placed on the tanker by W. R. Davis was
                                    350,000.00 dollars of which 50,000.00 dollars would be paid in
                                    cash and the remainder in petroleum products.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Josephus Daniels</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>